  "body": "When i tried to run simple script that only calls view methods of some smart contract, it fails with following exception:\r\n\r\n```\r\nTypeError: Cannot read property 'call' of null\r\n    at Object.<anonymous> ([redacted]/node_modules/@ethersproject/contracts/src.ts/index.ts:329:47)\r\n    at step ([redacted]/node_modules/@ethersproject/contracts/lib/index.js:48:23)\r\n    at Object.next ([redacted]/node_modules/@ethersproject/contracts/lib/index.js:29:53)\r\n    at fulfilled ([redacted]/node_modules/@ethersproject/contracts/lib/index.js:20:58)\r\n    at processTicksAndRejections (internal/process/task_queues.js:97:5)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Current Result\r\n\r\nAfter some digging around, i noticed that when i add any account to my network setting (e.g.: test address used in hardhat) it starts working as expected:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n    mainnet: {\r\n      url: 'https://mainnet.infura.io/v3/[redacted[',\r\n      accounts: {\r\n        mnemonic: \"test test test test test test test test test test test junk\"\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf accounts key is omitted, commented out, or it is empty array, it fails when running script.\r\n\r\nMy `package.json`:\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  \"name\": \"hardhat-project\",\r\n  \"devDependencies\": {\r\n    \"@nomiclabs/hardhat-ethers\": \"^2.0.2\",\r\n    \"@nomiclabs/hardhat-waffle\": \"^2.0.1\",\r\n    \"chai\": \"^4.3.4\",\r\n    \"ethereum-waffle\": \"^3.4.0\",\r\n    \"ethers\": \"^5.4.4\",\r\n    \"hardhat\": \"^2.6.0\",\r\n    \"hardhat-deploy\": \"^0.8.11\",\r\n    \"prettier\": \"^2.3.2\",\r\n    \"prettier-plugin-solidity\": \"^1.0.0-beta.17\",\r\n    \"solidity-coverage\": \"git+ssh://git@github.com/psychob/solidity-coverage.git\"\r\n  },\r\n  \"dependencies\": {\r\n    \"@openzeppelin/contracts\": \"^3.4.1\",\r\n    \"@uniswap/v2-periphery\": \"^1.1.0-beta.0\",\r\n    \"dotenv\": \"^10.0.0\"\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected Result\r\n\r\nEither:\r\n\r\n1. Script will fail at configuration phase, that account is required\r\n2. Script will run as expected, and only fail if method we are trying to run modifies state of blockchain",
